OL,3,CMan jailed for threatening to burn
OL,4,Cdown city's mosques in TikTok video
OL,6,FA father-of-four who made a TikTok
OL,7,Fvideo threatening to burn down every
OL,8,Fmosque in Newcastle has been jailed.
OL,10,FJames Aspin, 34, from Briardale Road,
OL,11,FBlyth, Northumberland, posted what a
OL,12,Fjudge called a "hugely offensive and
OL,13,Fdangerous" four-minute video on August
OL,14,F8, shortly after the Southport
OL,15,Fstabbings.
OL,17,FAspin was sentenced to 20 months in
OL,18,Fprison at Newcastle Crown Court after
OL,19,Fadmitting distributing a recording
OL,20,Fintending to stir up racial hatred.
